<subSubSection box="[107,1309,1123,1156]" pageId="209" pageNumber="488" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="209.[105,1313,729,1354]" box="[107,1309,1123,1156]" pageId="209" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[107,239,1123,1156]" pageId="209" pageNumber="488">Breeding.</emphasis>
A nursing female and an adult male with scrotal testes were found in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="209" pageNumber="488" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="209.[105,1313,729,1354]" pageId="209" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[105,343,1163,1196]" pageId="209" pageNumber="488">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Albuja’s Climbing Rat is nocturnal, terrestrial, and arboreal. It has been collected on the ground and 1-8 m high.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
